# MCP servers in this project

MCP configuration lives in **Cursor**, not in generated shell scripts in the repo.

1. **Edit Cursor MCP config**
   - Add or update server entries in `.cursor/mcp.json` (or Cursor Settings → MCP) per [Cursor MCP docs](https://docs.cursor.com/context/mcp).

2. **Secrets and env**
   - Put API keys and tokens in `.env` (local only; never commit) or in the `env` block of each server in MCP settings, as your team prefers.
   - Reference the same variable names Task Master expects where applicable (see project `env.template` and Taskmaster rules).

3. **No script templates in-repo**
   - Do not reintroduce a directory of `.template` launcher scripts; keep launch commands and env in Cursor’s MCP configuration so setup matches your current MCP layout.
